# .dockerignore — what the codemojex-edge-deliver build must NOT copy.
#
# The build context is this self-contained assets/ tree and the Dockerfile does
# `COPY . .`. Without this file that COPY drags in node_modules — ~134M of
# HOST-PLATFORM binaries (on a Mac: darwin-arm64 esbuild + rollup's native dep).
# Inside the linux image those binaries are wrong, and `pnpm install --frozen-lockfile`
# can treat the copied tree as already-satisfied and skip fetching the linux ones —
# so `vite build` then aborts with "you installed esbuild for another platform".
#
# Excluding node_modules forces a clean, in-image, linux-correct install from the
# lockfile (lockfileVersion 9.0 · pnpm 10.17.1) and shrinks the context to source.

# Dependencies — re-installed inside the image for the linux target.
node_modules
**/node_modules
.pnpm-store

# Build output — the game bundle is produced INSIDE the image (into /priv/static/game).
dist
*.tsbuildinfo

# OS / editor cruft.
.DS_Store
**/.DS_Store

# VCS metadata (the context is assets/, but be explicit).
.git
**/.git
